@Transcend and Impoetic, if it's all the same to you, let's lynch Mulch. I just want the game to end today and I feel really, really strongly about projectmatt being town. Neither of you have addressed my three separate reasons for townreading him: 1) Boon setting him up to be lynched upon a Dunker flip (Boon did the same to me and it makes a fuckton more sense for Boon to set up a townie than a buddy). Mulch countered this with vague assertions about me not knowing how Boon thinks which he CANNOT back up despite being asked twice. 2) Dunker acting like he and pjm were the same alignment which is the EXACT same thing that Boon was doing with you (Transcend). They set themselves up on opposite sides and tied two townies to each other. Their plan is blatantly obvious. 3) Projectmatt's own reaction to them mirrored mine. He wonders what the heck is going on, then speculates that it could be a Boon/Dunker team. <br>
<br>
I don't want to lynch a townread and give Mulch another shot at escaping the lynch. Graphic Design has been super low key and had some scummy moments (the Creature scumread mysteriously disappearing after I told him Creature was town through meta). You were so, so sure that Gerry was scum and I just caved in and let you have the lynch. If you think I'm town either way, trust me on this and lynch Mulch. Or at the very least acknowledge my towncase on Matt because I think it's airtight and I really don't want this to get to lylo. Still 99% confident game ends with a Mulch lynch.
